- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper focuses on analyzing achievable rates and power allocations for different transmission strategies in a CF-mMIMO system with limited capacity FHLs. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely because the paper deals with the transmission of CSI and data signals over FHLs connecting APs to the CU, and proposes low-complexity fronthaul capacity allocations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility because the paper deals with the design and optimization of a CF-mMIMO system with hardware impairments and limited capacity FHLs. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility because the paper deals with the transmission of data signals in a wireless communication system. 
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is unlikely because the paper does not deal with social or ethical issues related to computing.
